The paper deals with Sketch-Based Image Retrieval (SBIR), which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves a generative model that learns to generate images, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the model involves comparing the generated images to real images, which is a task in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the goal of the paper is to improve retrieval performance, which is a task in information retrieval (cs.IR).
